main: ^Boracay is a  resort island in the Western Visayas region of the Philippines and was was originally inhabited by the Ati people, but commercial development has led to leave and relocate.

c-0: ^Apart from its white sand beaches, Boracay is also famous for being one of the world's top destinations for relaxation. The island's indigenous Ati people say that the name of the island came from the Inati words "bora", meaning bubbles, and "bocay", meaning white.
